Noun \Rhap"sode\ (r[a^]p"s[=o]d) (Gr. Antiq.)


'''1.''' One who performs the poetry of a poet for an audience; not a writer of poetry: ''Socrates: And do the Epidaurians have contests of rhapsodes at the festival?'' (Plato's Ion)<br>
'''2.''' The interpreter of a poem: ''Socrates: Then you rhapsodists are the interpreters of the poets?'' (Plato's Ion)<br>
'''3.''' A rhapsodist.<br>